<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="151" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1158,1363]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1194,1219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">Remarks.</emphasis>
Maximum shoot size is 
<number box="[622,678,1195,1219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" value="1200.0">1200</number>
µm; undetermined nematocysts: 
<date box="[1077,1106,1195,1219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">
<number box="[1077,1091,1195,1219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" value="7.0">7</number>
x
</date>
<number box="[1106,1119,1195,1219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" value="3.0">3</number>
µm; perisarc tube usually annulated basally, occasionally distally, usually straight; pseudohydrotheca present, one whorl of filiform tentacles, hypostome salient and rounded-conical. The morphology is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sars, 1874" authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1874" box="[1009,1382,1267,1291]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Bougainvilliidae" genus="Rhizorhagium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="roseum">
<emphasis box="[1009,1256,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">Rhizorhagium roseum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sars" box="[1261,1382,1267,1291]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" refString="Sars, G. O. (1874) Bidrag til Kundskaben om Norges Hydroider. Forhandlinger i Videnskabsselskabet i Kristianina, 1873, 91 - 150." type="journal article" year="1874">
Sars, 
<number box="[1323,1382,1267,1291]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" value="1874.0">1874</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The absence of specimens with gonophores prevents an accurate identification. This is the first record of a 
<taxonomicName box="[151,338,1338,1363]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Bougainvilliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Bougainvilliidae</taxonomicName>
taxon in the Gorringe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
